{"TopicId":175498,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Detection event for Wheel broken?","CreatedByName":"cyberKerb","CreatedById":28891,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-31T13:14:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"cyberKerb","CreatedById":28891,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-31T13:14:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a GameEvent or function that fires when a wheel breaks?\u003Cbr\u003E\nSpecifically - when the\u00A0wheelDamage.isDamaged value get set to true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was hoping to get something to fire when this happens rather then constantly testing the value in a FixedUpdate piece of code.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried the GameEvent.onPartFailure(runthis)\u00A0 but that doesn\u0027t seem to fire for wheel breakages.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-08-16T23:35:56Z\u0022 title=\u002208/16/2019 11:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 16, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by cyberKerb\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sarbian","CreatedById":57146,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-31T16:11:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck when\u00A0onWheelRepaired is fired, who knows...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-05-31T16:14:06Z\u0022 title=\u002205/31/2018 04:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMay 31, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by sarbian\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cyberKerb","CreatedById":28891,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-05-31T16:31:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223390062\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527783118\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257146\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sarbian\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, sarbian said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheck when\u00A0onWheelRepaired \u003Cspan\u003E\uFEFF\u003C/span\u003Eis fired, who knows...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks Sarbian - I checked that as well just now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately it only fires on the EVA repair event. Propably fired under the event\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EwheelDamage.\u003C/span\u003EEventRepairExternal()\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve scoured the API for while this afternoon and I think my only option is a FixedUpdate check like the below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Epublic Boolean firedalready = false;\n\nprivate void FixedUpdate()\n{\n\tif (this.wheelDamage.isDamaged \u0026amp;\u0026amp; !this.firedalready) \n\t{\n\t\tthis.firedalready = true\n\t\trunMyRoutine()\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JPLRepo","CreatedById":114736,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-23T21:04:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223390081\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022175498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221527784299\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002228891\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wile1411\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/1/2018 at 2:31 AM, wile1411 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents ipsClearfix\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks Sarbian - I checked that as well just now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately it only fires on the EVA repair event. Propably fired under the event\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EwheelDamage.\u003C/span\u003EEventRepairExternal()\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve scoured the API for while this afternoon and I think my only option is a FixedUpdate check like the below.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003Epublic Boolean firedalready = false;\n\nprivate void FixedUpdate()\n{\n\tif (this.wheelDamage.isDamaged \u0026amp;\u0026amp; !this.firedalready) \n\t{\n\t\tthis.firedalready = true\n\t\trunMyRoutine()\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is about the only option you have.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cyberKerb","CreatedById":28891,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-07-26T10:35:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nokies - thanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}